      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DARKEST COLOUR (4) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at Healesville over 350m behind Mikado Mania (19.90) in a T3 Grade 6. Should be very hard to beat this time. KIOWA ICON (2) slotted in just off the lead from the wide draw last start and boxed on to finish third (22.66) at this track in a Grade 7 over 390m. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Winning chance. FLYING NARDO (3) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 4.5 lengths at Healesville in a handy 19.45 beating Unleash Gabbi. Deserves serious consideration again. BONNIE BEAUTIFUL (1) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
